{"componentChunkName":"component---src-templates-blog-post-js","path":"/agile-scrum-notes-09/","result":{"data":{"site":{"siteMetadata":{"title":"zehengl","author":"Zeheng Li"}},"markdownRemark":{"id":"7afe10a2-33e1-5c1d-94a4-18216aa20778","excerpt":"Principles in monitoring Scrum Projects Ideally, the TEAM should monitor its own progress The manager or Scrum Master should NOT micro- manage The Scrum Master…","html":"<h2>Principles in monitoring Scrum Projects</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Ideally, the TEAM should monitor its own progress</p>\n<ul>\n<li>The manager or Scrum Master should NOT micro- manage</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>The Scrum Master should try to provide the team visibility so that they can make informed decisions</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Common tracking mechanisms in Scrum</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Daily stand-up meetings</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Reviews and retrospectives</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Metrics</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Charts</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Information radiators</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Metrics</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>A metric is a standard for measuring or evaluating something.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>A measure is a quantity, a proportion, or a qualitative comparison of some kind.</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Quantity: “There are 25 open defect reports on the application as of today.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Proportion: “This week there are 10 percent fewer open defect reports than last week.”</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Qualitative comparison: “The new version of the software is easier to use than the old version.”</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Types of metrics</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Business</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>RTF (Running Tested Features)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Earned Business Value (EBV)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Net Present Value (NPV)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Internal Rate of Return (IRR)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Return on Investment (ROI)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Process</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Impediments cleared per iteration</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Impediments &#x26; User stories carried over the next iteration</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>User stories done per iteration</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Defects carried over the next iteration</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Team member loading</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Velocity</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Backlog size</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Project Testing</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Acceptance tests per story</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Defects count per story</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Escaped Defects per cycle</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Tests time to run</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Tests run per frequency</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Time to fix tests</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Do’s and Don’ts</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Measure only a few things that matter (just because it can be measured doesn’t mean it is important)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>It should be easy to calculate (ideally an automated process)</p>\n<ul>\n<li>If it is too cumbersome, either people won’t do it or it will be incorrect</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>It should be easy to explain and interpret</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>It should result in tangible action</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Behavior that you want to encourage OR</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Behavior that you want to discourage</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Use metrics to guide action, not for witch-hunts</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>In Scrum, team metrics are preferred</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Do NOT use metrics for performance appraisals</p>\n<ul>\n<li>It will usually result in perverse incentive to manipulate the number</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Charts in Scrum</h2>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Commonly used charts:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Burn-down, Burn-up charts</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Cumulative Flow Diagrams</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Progress Charts</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Risk profile graphs</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Others</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Charts are useful because:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>It indicates trends (trends are more important than absolute numbers)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>It is more “visual” (a picture is worth a thousand words)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Management loves charts!</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<h2>Burn-down Chart</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/59a5731fc82b2a5ccb56f285f069f717/9be90/burn-down-chart.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 41.21621621621622%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"burn-down-chart\"\n        title=\"burn-down-chart\"\n        src=\"/static/59a5731fc82b2a5ccb56f285f069f717/fcda8/burn-down-chart.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/59a5731fc82b2a5ccb56f285f069f717/12f09/burn-down-chart.png 148w,\n/static/59a5731fc82b2a5ccb56f285f069f717/e4a3f/burn-down-chart.png 295w,\n/static/59a5731fc82b2a5ccb56f285f069f717/fcda8/burn-down-chart.png 590w,\n/static/59a5731fc82b2a5ccb56f285f069f717/9be90/burn-down-chart.png 636w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2>Burn-down Chart Bar Style</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ea72c0fd4f1979c21dfa7a6b13feeeaf/d0cc0/burn-down-chart-bar-style.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 71.62162162162163%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"burn-down-chart-bar-style\"\n        title=\"burn-down-chart-bar-style\"\n        src=\"/static/ea72c0fd4f1979c21dfa7a6b13feeeaf/fcda8/burn-down-chart-bar-style.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/ea72c0fd4f1979c21dfa7a6b13feeeaf/12f09/burn-down-chart-bar-style.png 148w,\n/static/ea72c0fd4f1979c21dfa7a6b13feeeaf/e4a3f/burn-down-chart-bar-style.png 295w,\n/static/ea72c0fd4f1979c21dfa7a6b13feeeaf/fcda8/burn-down-chart-bar-style.png 590w,\n/static/ea72c0fd4f1979c21dfa7a6b13feeeaf/d0cc0/burn-down-chart-bar-style.png 732w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2>Burn-up and Burn-down Chart</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/ce646e7e7f2a32992bab1994d54c508b/7f450/burn-up-burn-down-chart.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"burn-up-burn-down-chart\"\n        title=\"burn-up-burn-down-chart\"\n        src=\"/static/ce646e7e7f2a32992bab1994d54c508b/1c72d/burn-up-burn-down-chart.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/ce646e7e7f2a32992bab1994d54c508b/a80bd/burn-up-burn-down-chart.jpg 148w,\n/static/ce646e7e7f2a32992bab1994d54c508b/1c91a/burn-up-burn-down-chart.jpg 295w,\n/static/ce646e7e7f2a32992bab1994d54c508b/1c72d/burn-up-burn-down-chart.jpg 590w,\n/static/ce646e7e7f2a32992bab1994d54c508b/7f450/burn-up-burn-down-chart.jpg 728w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2>Cumulative Flow Diagram</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/12a9d56955e1d4d9c30ef35a89ebea61/6aca1/cumulative-flow-diagram.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 62.83783783783784%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"cumulative-flow-diagram\"\n        title=\"cumulative-flow-diagram\"\n        src=\"/static/12a9d56955e1d4d9c30ef35a89ebea61/1c72d/cumulative-flow-diagram.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/12a9d56955e1d4d9c30ef35a89ebea61/a80bd/cumulative-flow-diagram.jpg 148w,\n/static/12a9d56955e1d4d9c30ef35a89ebea61/1c91a/cumulative-flow-diagram.jpg 295w,\n/static/12a9d56955e1d4d9c30ef35a89ebea61/1c72d/cumulative-flow-diagram.jpg 590w,\n/static/12a9d56955e1d4d9c30ef35a89ebea61/6aca1/cumulative-flow-diagram.jpg 650w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2>Parking Lot Diagram</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/93e5cf95039c064091d52629ace801f6/6af66/parking-lot-diagram.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 68.91891891891892%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"parking-lot-diagram\"\n        title=\"parking-lot-diagram\"\n        src=\"/static/93e5cf95039c064091d52629ace801f6/fcda8/parking-lot-diagram.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/93e5cf95039c064091d52629ace801f6/12f09/parking-lot-diagram.png 148w,\n/static/93e5cf95039c064091d52629ace801f6/e4a3f/parking-lot-diagram.png 295w,\n/static/93e5cf95039c064091d52629ace801f6/fcda8/parking-lot-diagram.png 590w,\n/static/93e5cf95039c064091d52629ace801f6/6af66/parking-lot-diagram.png 640w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2>Escaped defects found</h2>\n<p>Escaped Defects Found counts number of new escaped defects found over period of time (day, week, month).</p>\n<h2>Velocity Chart</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/a700c8a4b3e69f70c983cf3ee9bcf96c/acf8f/velocity-chart.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 66.21621621621621%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"velocity-chart\"\n        title=\"velocity-chart\"\n        src=\"/static/a700c8a4b3e69f70c983cf3ee9bcf96c/fcda8/velocity-chart.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/a700c8a4b3e69f70c983cf3ee9bcf96c/12f09/velocity-chart.png 148w,\n/static/a700c8a4b3e69f70c983cf3ee9bcf96c/e4a3f/velocity-chart.png 295w,\n/static/a700c8a4b3e69f70c983cf3ee9bcf96c/fcda8/velocity-chart.png 590w,\n/static/a700c8a4b3e69f70c983cf3ee9bcf96c/efc66/velocity-chart.png 885w,\n/static/a700c8a4b3e69f70c983cf3ee9bcf96c/c83ae/velocity-chart.png 1180w,\n/static/a700c8a4b3e69f70c983cf3ee9bcf96c/acf8f/velocity-chart.png 1340w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2>Progress Chart / Kanban</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/06c02e051ed9fdd689509fa65d506ce8/f6b72/kanban-board.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 49.32432432432432%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"kanban-board\"\n        title=\"kanban-board\"\n        src=\"/static/06c02e051ed9fdd689509fa65d506ce8/fcda8/kanban-board.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/06c02e051ed9fdd689509fa65d506ce8/12f09/kanban-board.png 148w,\n/static/06c02e051ed9fdd689509fa65d506ce8/e4a3f/kanban-board.png 295w,\n/static/06c02e051ed9fdd689509fa65d506ce8/fcda8/kanban-board.png 590w,\n/static/06c02e051ed9fdd689509fa65d506ce8/f6b72/kanban-board.png 615w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2>Niko Niko Calendar</h2>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/2368e988ed57d1fbafa0e5a5795ed72e/5a190/niko-niko-calendar.png\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 54.05405405405405%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/png;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"niko-niko-calendar\"\n        title=\"niko-niko-calendar\"\n        src=\"/static/2368e988ed57d1fbafa0e5a5795ed72e/fcda8/niko-niko-calendar.png\"\n        srcset=\"/static/2368e988ed57d1fbafa0e5a5795ed72e/12f09/niko-niko-calendar.png 148w,\n/static/2368e988ed57d1fbafa0e5a5795ed72e/e4a3f/niko-niko-calendar.png 295w,\n/static/2368e988ed57d1fbafa0e5a5795ed72e/fcda8/niko-niko-calendar.png 590w,\n/static/2368e988ed57d1fbafa0e5a5795ed72e/5a190/niko-niko-calendar.png 800w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<h2>Information radiators</h2>\n<p>“An information radiator displays information in a place where passers by can see it. With information radiators, the passers by don’t need to ask any question; the information simply hits them as they pass.”</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Invented by Alistair Cockburn</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Team members can view the current state of the project : schedules, tasks, progress, issues</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Scrum teams should use it to make progress (or lack of) visible</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/3b8f7ac400e3e905730e2da8261453c5/8608d/information-radiators1.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 56.08108108108109%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"information-radiators1\"\n        title=\"information-radiators1\"\n        src=\"/static/3b8f7ac400e3e905730e2da8261453c5/1c72d/information-radiators1.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/3b8f7ac400e3e905730e2da8261453c5/a80bd/information-radiators1.jpg 148w,\n/static/3b8f7ac400e3e905730e2da8261453c5/1c91a/information-radiators1.jpg 295w,\n/static/3b8f7ac400e3e905730e2da8261453c5/1c72d/information-radiators1.jpg 590w,\n/static/3b8f7ac400e3e905730e2da8261453c5/8608d/information-radiators1.jpg 638w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Most popular Information radiators are:</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p>Task Boards</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Big Visible charts (Includes burn down charts)</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p>Continuous Integration build health Indicators (Including lava lamps and street lights)</p>\n</li>\n</ul>\n<p><span\n      class=\"gatsby-resp-image-wrapper\"\n      style=\"position: relative; display: block; margin-left: auto; margin-right: auto; max-width: 590px; \"\n    >\n      <a\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-link\"\n    href=\"/static/81434d20c506df69a63e6b7cc427eb68/8608d/information-radiators2.jpg\"\n    style=\"display: block\"\n    target=\"_blank\"\n    rel=\"noopener\"\n  >\n    <span\n    class=\"gatsby-resp-image-background-image\"\n    style=\"padding-bottom: 75%; position: relative; bottom: 0; left: 0; background-image: url('data:image/jpeg;base64,'); background-size: cover; display: block;\"\n  ></span>\n  <img\n        class=\"gatsby-resp-image-image\"\n        alt=\"information-radiators2\"\n        title=\"information-radiators2\"\n        src=\"/static/81434d20c506df69a63e6b7cc427eb68/1c72d/information-radiators2.jpg\"\n        srcset=\"/static/81434d20c506df69a63e6b7cc427eb68/a80bd/information-radiators2.jpg 148w,\n/static/81434d20c506df69a63e6b7cc427eb68/1c91a/information-radiators2.jpg 295w,\n/static/81434d20c506df69a63e6b7cc427eb68/1c72d/information-radiators2.jpg 590w,\n/static/81434d20c506df69a63e6b7cc427eb68/8608d/information-radiators2.jpg 638w\"\n        sizes=\"(max-width: 590px) 100vw, 590px\"\n        style=\"width:100%;height:100%;margin:0;vertical-align:middle;position:absolute;top:0;left:0;\"\n        loading=\"lazy\"\n        decoding=\"async\"\n      />\n  </a>\n    </span></p>\n<p>Effective Information Radiators should be :</p>\n<ul>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Simple</strong>: Should be Brief and concise.</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Stark</strong>: Should display the progress and expose problems. Errors should not be masked, rather used to improve the work and performance</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Current</strong>: Information displayed should be current</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Transient</strong>: The problems and errors shouldn’t be there on the chart for long; once the problem has been rectified, it should be taken off</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Influential</strong>: Influences the team members and management and empowers the whole team to take decisions</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Highly</strong> visible</p>\n</li>\n<li>\n<p><strong>Minimal</strong> in number</p>\n</li>\n</ul>","frontmatter":{"title":"Agile Scrum Note 09: Monitoring Scrum Projects","date":"2016-01-28","description":"Tools and techniques to monitoring Scrum projects."}}},"pageContext":{"slug":"/agile-scrum-notes-09/","previous":{"fields":{"slug":"/agile-scrum-notes-08/"},"frontmatter":{"tags":["agile","scrum"],"title":"Agile Scrum Note 08: Estimation"}},"next":{"fields":{"slug":"/agile-scrum-notes-10/"},"frontmatter":{"tags":["agile","scrum"],"title":"Agile Scrum Note 10: Advanced Concepts"}}}},"staticQueryHashes":["63159454"]}